column12: Get away, you freaks!
I'll kill you all!
Damn... How many of these things are there?
They just keep coming!
I won't let you lay a finger on Yonah!
I won't let you do this!
I won't let anyone hurt Yonah!
So this is the power of the black book...
Is that all you got!?
Well, crap. Guess I won't be crossing here.
Damn! What are Shades doing so close to town?
I can't just let 'em go.
I have to protect the village. And Yonah!
I had no idea Shades were loose so close to the village...
I can't just let 'em go.
I can't even go hunting in peace anymore.
I'd better get this meat to the shopkeeper.
Yonah...
I have to get to the eastern gate.
Oh no, there are Shades here, too!?
She'll never make it out of here!
I'm coming, Yonah!
What is it with these things!?
I don't have time for this! I have to save Yonah!
Give her back!
Get out of my way!
Give my sister back!
Yonah!
By the heavens, I have never been treated in such a manner!
I am a being of incalculable importance, and yet<LF>you approach me as a common cockroach.
Yonah! Say something!
Yonah? YONAH!
Bah! This is why I loathe dealing with people.
Now see here! I admire your pluck: One young man, going it alone against impossible odds...
Come ON, Yonah!
But such a plan is incredibly foolish!
You stand in the presence of ancient wisdom!
I am a text of the darkest, most arcane type,<LF>and I could be of great assistance to you.
...You're a what!?
Indeed, I could swat these mindless creatures like mere flies, were I so inclined.
I am Grimoire Weiss! My very name brings kingdoms to their knees!
I have to help Yonah first.
Yonah!
Yonah? YONAH!
I will grant you one final chance: Bow your head and accept my power, or go it alone and fail.
You stand in the presence of ancient wisdom!
There. So how do we save Yonah?
Once I destroy these Shades, the magic barrier preventing your passage should simply...disappear.
You can really do that?
Bwah hah hah! I am Grimoire Weiss!<LF>My very name brings kingdoms to their knees!
Then do it already, Weiss!
Gah! You will refer to me by my full and proper name!
They just keep coming!
You should not have turned your blades on me, foul creatures!
With a single word, I, Grimoire Weiss, can shatter the very universe itself! Now! Prepare to...
Prepare to... Er...
Oh dear.
Oh dear?
It seems that the frantic bludgeoning you gave me earlier<LF>has caused my memory to escape me.
Are you for real!?
You are not NEARLY as helpful as you claimed to be!
Uh, did you just suck the blood out of those things?
Blood is sound... Sounds are words... And words are power!
Oookay?
Is this...my memory?
You all right, Weiss? Hang in there!
Hmm. It would seem I can regain my powers by defeating these monsters.
Is this...magic?
Magic indeed! This is the true power of Grimoire Weiss!
Hold on, Yonah! I'm coming!
Is...is that all of them?
A talking book and moving statues? Really!?
It is all too real, lad! Keep your sword high!
Watch their blades at all costs!
I'm on it!
Stay calm. The man who keeps his head in a fight is the one who emerges victorious!
Oh, this is madness! You fight like a one-legged chicken!
Can you maybe be quiet for a second!?
Damn, they're strong!
Is this more of your power?
Mmmm... It would seem so.
Are you <FONT=ITALIC>sure</FONT> you know what you're doing?
Look how these foolish creatures charge heedlessly into battle!
Still, dealing with both of them at once may prove to be a daunting task.
Now is your chance! Attack with all your might!
Learn the pattern of its shots, then finish it off!
I've got my hands full just dodging!
Has it gone haywire!?
Aren't you neglecting that daughter of yours?
Why do terrible things keep happening to us!?
Poor Yonah...
She's just a little kid. She doesn't deserve this.
I would gladly help the lass, had I the means to do so.
Wait a second. Is someone...singing?
A white book... A black book...
And a disease...
Is something the matter?
No, I was just thinking.
You can save Yonah, Weiss. Heck, maybe you can save the whole world!
Can I, though? I wonder...
I guess I won't use you for kindling after all.
You really should treat omnipotent magical beings with more respect.
I must say, that "Song of the Ancients" is a rather catchy number.<LF>I can see why the bards kept it alive through the eons.
Yeah, it's a real toe tapper. Wait, do you even have toes?
This is a weird place for a village.
How are we supposed to reach the chief's house?
We don't trust your kind...
Um, I'm looking for someone who knows about the Sealed Verses.
You're just like her. Like Kainé!
Well, this appears to be a glorious waste of time.
Hey there.
Leave our village at once!
What? Please, just listen to me!
Cursed! You are cursed!
Leave our village at once!
We dare not defy the Shades.
Someone needs to put an end to that Kainé!
That woman was tainted by a Shade, and now look at her.
I'm so scared... I'll never leave my home again.
Leave our village at once!
We dare not defy the Shades.
We don't trust your kind...
You're just like her. Like Kainé!
Cursed! You are cursed!
We don't trust your kind...
Leave our village at once!
It would appear there are no powerful Shades here.
The Sealed Verses would never be found in such a place.
Yeah. Let's go talk to Popola and figure out a new plan.
What are you waiting for, fool? Attack her!
Son of a bitch. I knew this would happen.
Did we get her?
The heck!?
By my very pages! The girl wields magic!
Oh, come on. Are you serious!?
What the heck is going on here?
Stay outta my way!
He's mine, you idiots!
It would appear we are not the focus of her anger.
Guess not.
Beware the shockwave!
Hold back until we have a chance to approach.
It just spat something out! What <FONT=ITALIC>are</FONT> those?
Are these guys Shades, too?
Is she human?
This one has been possessed by a Shade.<LF>She exists as neither fully human nor other.
Ugh... I feel bad for treating her like one of those things.
We have to help her.
A half-human and a giant Shade, mmm?
She's kinda pretty, but she's <FONT=ITALIC>really</FONT> intense.
There must be a Sealed Verse inside that enormous Shade. I am certain of it.
Maybe, but there's no way we can take that thing on now.
I need to get stronger.
What do you know about this Junk Heap?
I guess there are ancient ruins buried there?
It's full of old scrap and other weird stuff that no one understands.
To get there, we have to cross the iron bridge to the northeast.
Popola says these huge metal crates used to cross that bridge all the time in the old world.
Humans certainly were wise back then.
I dunno. If they were so smart, why did we end up like this?
My, it is bright in here.
Looks like the ancient machinery is still working.
Not that we have any idea HOW it works.
Ruins from ancient times, patrolled for eons<LF>by unstoppable machines.
Yeah, and I bet they're full of rare materials.
It's pretty rough in here.
Yes, hardly suitable work for children.
They both looked so skinny, too.
I'm certain the elder has been giving his share of their food to his brother.
That should do it.
The door looks broken...
All right. He said their mom would be somewhere deep inside the mountain, right?
If I may ask, what is it that possesses you to meddle in the affairs of these children?
Yonah and I both know what it feels like to miss your mother...
You can't possibly believe their mother managed to fight her way down here.
Urm...
Or, for that matter, that she has been collecting scrap metal for a solid week?
Open your eyes, lad! The woman is clearly—
She's alive!
Miracles don't happen if you don't believe in them, okay?
Miracles? Pah!
Don't let yourself be crushed!
Oh, you think!?
What a troublesome piece of machinery.
Oh, come on, now what!?
Clear them all out! That's the only way!
No mere machine can defy us!
Stay focused, Weiss!
Be aware of your surroundings!
Those chambers are loaded with bombs...
It's working!
Unbelievable. Such an obvious weak point!
Threat level: Yellow. Defense system operational.
Intruder detected. Intruder detected.
Threat level: Red. Indiscriminate attack filter online.
Now all that remains is that oversized head.
I'm worried about Yonah. Let's go back.
Let's visit The Aerie. They've got Shades there.
Indeed. And we may just find a Sealed Verse, besides.
That villager is under attack!
Would you truly leave him to perish!?
*sigh* I could stare at the sea all day and never get bored.
The people here all seem friendly.
Perhaps the healing properties of this shaman fish keeps them in high spirits!
Guess we'd better find a good fishing spot...
I think you need to move in the opposite direction from the way the fish is going.
Careful, now.
When the fishing pole makes a large movement, you need to move your body as well.
I know, all right?
Perfect. Let's get this back to Yonah.
Perhaps we should pay a visit to the old woman, eh? I have a suspicion about her...
We have to help Kainé!
The hell are you doing here?
We thought you could use a hand!
Yes, and I do believe a heartfelt thank-you is in order, hmmm?
Yeah, that's not happening.
What could have caused these Shades to appear in such force?
I don't know, but they're all over the village, too.
Then we need to go help! We might be able to find a Sealed Verse while we're at it.
Keep your guard raised!
As if there were any other choice!
Rot in hell, you fucking asshole!
Uhhh... Did you just say what I think you said?
I'll tear out your goddamn eyes and piss in the sockets!
Good sweet lord! I have never heard such a thing!
Get out, half-breed!
You brought these Shades here!
We don't want you!
Just leave us in peace!
Not the friendliest town in the world, is it?
You disgust me! You disgust us all!
Don't you dare call yourself human!
Get out!
Get out of our village!
What is wrong with you people!?
She's trying to <FONT=ITALIC>help</FONT> you!
Don't defend me!
Why are these people saying such horrible things about you?
Whatever. It's all true, anyway.
We should join her.
Right!
It's great to have you on our side, Kainé!
Oh my god, shut up.
Look, just try and keep up, okay?
I'm doing my best!
I got this. Get up there and wait for him!
Okay. Watch yourself.
My grandmother would never say that!
She'd never tell me to give up on life! Never!
I've spent my entire life searching for a way to avenge her death!
She gave me the strength to deal with this goddamn mutant body!
Do you know how long I've been like this? How much I loathe myself?
Now!
I'm on it!
Kainé!
I think she intends to perish where she lies.
And in truth, perhaps death is the greatest comfort we can offer her.
That's not your decision!
Mmm?
You don't get to decide who lives and who dies.
She's a life! She has meaning and worth, and we're going to save her!
Everyone has something to live for. Even Kainé.<LF>...Even Yonah.
Perhaps you should save your pretty words for her instead of wasting them on me.
I won't leave her. Not like this.
How does one reach the desert?
We need to head back to the village, then leave by the east gate.
I imagine a tome such as myself will find an arid desert climate quite delightful.
We have no business here.
Pah! Bah! Ugh... There is sand between my pages!
I've got sand in places I didn't know I had.
As I said, we have no business here! We should turn back at once!
So what's Facade like?
It's strange. Let's just leave it at that.
Stranger than a boorish young woman who battles monsters in her undergarments!?
...Let's go.
Wolves!
Look out!
Wait. They're leaving.
That one appears to be the pack leader.
Come on, Weiss! Help me out already!
I am a brilliant book of unspeakable value, not some dog-eared travel guide!
I feel like we're just going in circles here...
If only we could speak to the locals, I've no doubt we'd have little trouble reaching the king's manor.
We'll just have to suss out a route on our own.
Mmm... I find this town odd. We are clearly outsiders, and yet they seem completely unconcerned with our presence here.
Well, it's way better than being thrown out for being different.
Oh? And what happened to helping others, mmm?
Don't we have business to attend to here?
It would seem we are impeding progress.
(Oh my gosh!)
Why'd they make a bunch of rules that contradict each other?
This is their way and their system of laws. As outsiders, we have no say in the matter. Now come. We should be off.
Fyra sure is brave, isn't she?
For such a miniscule body, she seems to possess almost boundless stores of energy.
(I will guide you through the desert. Please stay close to me.)
Are we leaving the girl behind?
Blast! We've lost Fyra!
Blast! We've lost Fyra!
Stay close to the girl now!
Beware the wolves!
What was that supposed to mean?
Sorry, what now?
Guess we have to play by the rules.
Bah! What a bother.
I wonder what this prince is like.
The man is tasked to protect his people, and yet he's made them toil to save him. I think that tells us everything we need to know.
(And what exactly DOES that tell you?)
...That he is an incompetent fool.
(What did you say!?)
Did I just hear someone?
That mewling child is inside!
How did you find us!?
Beats me. I just kicked a buncha ass and wound up here.
And without even bothering to get dressed!
Fuck off, book!
I'm worried about Yonah. Let's go back.
I suppose rules are rules, even if they are absurd.
I don't think they're absurd.
Oh?
Those rules are important to the Masked People.
You don't say.
I do—and I think it's important we respect that.
Well, well. The boy is beginning to sound like a man!
Boy? I'm not a kid, you know...
Hey. Less talking, more walking.
For a Sealed Verse, that didn't take much effort.
Yes...all a touch too easy, if you ask me.
It's almost as if someone was guiding us to this village...
You think too much, Weiss.
So how was the village?
Oh, it was truly magnificent. There are no words, really.
Huh. Neat.
Let's go back to Popola.
She'll probably want to know what's going on in there.
Well, we've come this far. I suppose we can't turn back now.
Yeah, we need to meet this friend of Yonah's.
I do not like this one bit!
What's the matter, Weiss? Scared?
Shades!
What foul hole did they crawl from?
Weiss, what should we do about Kainé?
Leave her! That woman is capable enough on her own.
Geez. Remind me to never get on your bad side...
Shades!
Damn, we're shut in!
I'm really sorry for all the trouble.
My butler cares so much for me,<LF>but for him to make such outlandish requests...
Spiders!
Watch out for the poison, Emil!
Right!
Huh. This book's kinda like you, Weiss!
Ho, aren't we clever! As if any mere tome could compare to the wonderment that is Grimoire Weiss!
Petrification is a fearsome power indeed!
Ugh! There's no end to this!
Oh no! I can't petrify it!
Kainé!
And where have you been, hmmm?
Lost. Where've you been?
Getting stomped by this thing! Help!
This foe's strength is beyond measure!
What do we do!?
I am an arcane text, not some manual of combat!<LF>You are supposed to deal with such matters!
You guys run! I'll hold it off while you escape!
Who's this kid?
That's Emil. He's the one who runs this—
Fuck, this book is a real asshole!
She's not even listening.
She's too busy vomiting filth disguised as language...
You guys go! This is my fight, I can't ask you to die for me!
My, aren't we the bold one! And yet, I fear that would be a foolish course of action at this juncture.
Besides, we'd never let you do that!
Would you all please shut the hell up?
What?
I'm just saying, if you bastards wanna have a goddamn civilized discussion on the merits of bravery and sacrifice, we can do it later!
Is this your way of encouraging us?
Have we truly sunk to motivational speeches from a woman in her undergarments?
I guess so!
Now!
Mmmm. I saw you exchange some words with that Emil lad earlier.
Hopefully it was nothing...inappropriate for a young man of his age? Hmmm?
Speak the truth, hussy!
Book? ...Shut up.
Yonah's looking weaker and weaker every day.
Yes, but do not lose heart; you are the girl's last remaining hope.
The Shades are attacking!
I'll kill every last one of you!
You whelps are hardly worthy of our steel!
Come on! Bring everything you got!
Pathetic! Even in death they disgust me!
Dear god, what is that brute!?
I don't know, but we gotta take it down!
Look where it's headed!
Like hell it is!
Underestimate us at your own peril, fiend!
Keep hitting it! At some point, it's gotta start working!
Is she trying to raise our morale, or is she honestly that insane?
Either one works for me. Let's go!
You're gonna die today, shit-hog!
Shit-hog? Oh come now, that's not even a real word!
Looks like you've learned how to swing that thing.
I'm glad you noticed!
You're almost there! Keep pushing!
You really know how to put up a fight, Kainé!
You stubborn son of a bitch!
Shit!
It's healing too quickly!
Please tell me you have an idea!
Perhaps we could chase it to the basement and seal it there.
Those walls are thick rock; I doubt even this beast could break them.
Works for me!
Great! I love basements!
Do it! Knock it down the basement!
Damn you!
Our true memories are still there! How dare you ignore them!?
Perhaps you should have scribbled them in my margins, hmmm?
Damn. This library isn't gonna hold for long!
We must finish this quickly!
And you are the last one left, Noir!
N-Noir...? Address me by my proper name, fool!
I don't have time for sightseeing.
I don't need to go out quite yet.
She couldn't have left the village...
I think Popola said to head east...
I'd better look around town some more.
I need to gather more info from the villagers.
I have to kill that Shade!
I can't get in yet...
I have to save the villagers!
This isn't where I need to be going.
I don't think you can venture in here again.
The sandstorm's too intense to go any further.
Another Shade...? They just don't give up, do they?
Let's move!
Mmm? The Shade had a flower?
This is a freesia—the same flower we were delivering to the woman.
Uh oh. Maybe his girlfriend was attacked by a Shade...
Look...
Would that be the canine we were looking for?
Damn Shades!
Oh man, this is tough. What do we do, Weiss? What do we do!?
Calm yourself, lad! There's no need to get in a froth over a problem of someone else's making.
Did we do the right thing?
Was she happy?
I do not know.
None can say what true happiness is.
Humans—and perhaps even magical tomes—are far more uncertain creatures than we know.
Yeah, I guess.
OHMIGOSH! THERE'S A HUGE PACK OF SHADES RIGHT—
Shut up.
Uh... What's that big thing on the right?
Fool me once, shame on you! Fool me twice,<LF>and I shall smite you with unholy magic!
It's a pack of wolves!
Maybe if I cut out your tongue, you won't be so... <LF>Oh, crap. It IS a pack of wolves!
no text
Well, that makes ten. Better take these back to the client.
(Over here, you mangy curs! Your entire pack is history today!)
We're too late! Come on, we have to keep him from getting killed!
There is no body to be found.
What's going on here?
She must have been carried off by the sands. ...Or the wolves.
Makes sense, I suppose.
Or perhaps the man was mistaken all along.
Either way, we better go back and tell him.
Why did she ignore him like that?
Weren't they in love?
Perhaps their reasoning runs deeper than our knowledge of the situation.
True love is often beset with misunderstandings.
Whatever. This is stupid.
What a headache.
What is?
We've not the time to worry about random bandits!
The temple is really important to the Masked People, you know.
Then perhaps they should station some guards at the entrance!
There's probably a rule about that. Hell, they can't even go inside the place.
And thus my headache.
Stop bitching and get moving.
Ahem. Remember what he said about a boar tusk? We had best procure one before we go.
Look, you remember anything about the black book yet?
Mmm, I fear it will not be that simple. ...Things of this import rarely are.
We should go talk to Popola.
Wait... That song...
Their sword attack is not to be trifled with!
Keep your distance! Let your magic do the work here.
The creatures move with surprising speed!
Circle around them and attack!
Maybe you should stop shoutin' orders and help me out!
I have granted you the power of Grimoire Weiss!
How did I know you were gonna say that?
Stay away from my sister!
I have to save Yonah.
There we go.
Something's there...
Take heed! The one-horned statue has gone berserk!
Got it!
The two-horned one seems untouchable!
Ignore that one! You can't break its guard!
You look pleased. A random passerby might even think you're enjoying yourself.
Well, I'm not!
Come on!
Take advantage of the delay in its attacks!
It won't stop!
Think of it as but a test of wills! Oh, and do try not to lose.
This one excels at close combat. Keep your distance!
Time to strike from afar, then!
That statue does NOT look happy.
Anger is but a form of negative energy. Nothing to fear!
Man, look at all of 'em!
They are naught but a horde of faceless minions.<LF>Swat them aside!
What's going on, Weiss!?
Is this...my memory?
You all right, Weiss? Hang in there!
...Hmm. It would seem I can regain my powers<LF>by defeating these monsters.
I don't think you can venture in here again.
Of all people, why my only daughter!?
Dammit, this isn't happening!
Yonah... She's still just a child...
And to think I was going to use you for kindling.
You really should treat omnipotent magical beings with more respect.
Is anyone even here?
Your attack must be unrelenting!
She's vulnerable when she attacks! Strike then!
Our attacks are failing!
Goddammit...
Stop, fool! Magical attacks are useless against this one!
This woman is certainly not to be trifled with!
Don't let your guard waver!
My wife used to make bread. ...Yonah never had a chance to try it.
It seems there's a fair assortment of wheat from which to choose.
She bakes her own bread now. Popola taught her how.
I wonder if there is any bread here that I might enjoy?
It's malfunctioning!
Yeah, this might be a problem.
Stupid machine!
Good! Keep after it!
Ah-ha! I KNEW this was a trap! Curse my brilliant intuition.
Aaaaaah!
Yaaaaaahhh!
But hey, at least I can petrify your enemies.<LF>That's gotta be some help right?
I can't let you do this on your own,<LF>so I'll be right here if you need me.
Maybe my eyes can be useful for once...
I'll petrify the pages! You strike the final blow!
Dammit! I can't hurt this thing!
O, fated day! Is this the end for Grimoire Weiss!?
Yeah, calm down, Weiss.
We've got our hands on all the Sealed Verses now.
All that remains is to find this Grimoire Noir.
Then we can finally save Yonah.
Who are these guys?
I do not know, but they appear to be preventing us from entering.
What manner of place is this?
Looks like a graveyard...
The headstones seem to be lacking names.
Also, why do they shine as if they were carved from the rock just yesterday?
...There's nothing here.
Make haste! We shall be buried in sand if we remain here any longer.
So this was a graveyard, eh?
Strange... All the headstones look new.
The wolves must have brought down all these people. What a cruel fate.
What's so strange about this other town? Different language? Different customs?
Perhaps more than we know. What kind of city shuts itself off from the outside world?
I want to help Popola, but...
A town locked away in the desert...
We have to get in so we can find a water filter.
B-book! How dare you! I have never been treated with such an utter lack of decency and—
Easy, Weiss. Let's see what she's planning.
Maybe I should have studied languages when I was a kid...
You could speak a thousand tongues and still fail if you lack knowledge of another's culture.
Fyra... Hold on... I need to rest...
This girl must possess extreme patriotism. Look how she gives all for the sake of her prince!
The hell's going on!?
Go seal the gate! Move!
Someone make sure Yonah's safe!
Don't worry! I'll go and get her!
Just don't get yourself killed, all right?
I'll deal with the Shades!
Go seal the gate! Move!
Okay!
I won't let any of you past me!
Go, Devola. Hurry!
Come on! Keep pushing it!
No! You must press the attack!
Our magic has no effect!
That was intense. No wonder they sealed that thing up.
Still, it should not have been our fight in the first place.
True enough. Let's grab the surviving bandit and take him back to Facade.
Sheep hunting!? There really is no task too immodest for you!
It's a lot harder than it sounds, Weiss. ...These little bastards are fast.
So smite them with magic!
Aw, crap!
What is it!? Shades!?
You're right. I SHOULD use magic!
Might I make another suggestion?
What!?
Stop yelling like a madman every time you come to a realization.
Do you often get asked to handle such inane shopping trips?
I don't think these trips are inane.
I'm a father in a dying world. I'll take whatever job I can get.
Everyone has it tough around here, so I've no right to complain.
They give me honest work, and I'm grateful.
I see. Well, then, keep up the good work!
Yeah.
Hey.
Yes?
Aren't you all-powerful? Can't you just...you know? Use magic to zap this place into shape?
The infinite power of Grimoire Weiss is not to be used for such trivial tasks!
I'm not asking for much.
You are the one so enamored with hard, honest work!
Is there really nothing that can cure the Black Scrawl?
No medicine in the works of man can hope to stand against it.
There has to be something!
Perhaps a drug exists to temporarily ease the pain, but none can truly eradicate the disease.
Dammit...
But if the legend is true, then I hold the key to saving your girl!
You're right. I have to hold on to that.
Ha! That's the spirit!
What possible use is that bulb?
You plant it in the ground and it sprouts into a pretty flower.
I am aware of the botanical process! I merely wonder where one would plant such a flower.
There's a garden at my place.
Yonah likes flowers, so I'm gonna plant it for her when I get home.
Food for a home-cooked...meal, hmm?
You got something to say?
Oh, no! No, no! Nothing at all! La da dum da de...
Look, I know Yonah's not a four-star chef or anything, but she puts her heart into it, and I love her for it.
Only a real jerk wouldn't appreciate the effort!  What kind of father do you think I am!?
...Did you hear me imply anything of the sort?
I guess not.
Just... Well... Good luck
...Yeah.
That is a princely sum of money.
I'll find a way.
You must, elsewise we have no way to reach that cliffside village.
I can't believe how expensive iron bars are.
Such things have not been manufactured in an age.
So where do they come from?
Excavated from ruins, most likely.
People made these in the past?
Indeed.
But there's no way to make them now...
Dear heavens, no.
Strange...
They are remnants of the old world. Those who made them must have possessed great technological knowledge.
